'\" t
.TH CWE 7 "2026-06-15" "CWE Top 25 (2025)" "Software Weakness Reference"
.SH NAME
cwe \- index of KEV\-referenced Common Weakness Enumerations
.SH DESCRIPTION
This manual set documents the 2025 CWE Top 25 (published by MITRE/CISA on December 11, 2025) together with every other CWE that appears in the CISA Known Exploited Vulnerabilities (KEV) catalog. 183 weaknesses are documented in total.
.PP
26 pages are hand\-curated with a description, mitigation and a vulnerable\->fixed code example per ecosystem (Node.js, Python, Java, Go, PHP; C/C++ for the memory\-safety classes). The remainder are KEV stubs: MITRE name and description plus the list of exploited CVEs, pending curated examples.
.PP
Every page has a \fBKNOWN EXPLOITED VULNERABILITIES\fR section listing the CVEs CISA maps to that weakness. To read one, run \fBman\fR with its identifier, e.g. \fBman cwe\-78\fR. The KEV column below is the count of exploited CVEs.
